    "body": "Problem: `nvim_win_get_config()` does not return a window's `style`.\r\n\r\nSolution: always include it, and document `style=\"\"`.\r\n\r\nAlways included so it can be used reciprocally with `nvim_open_win()` or\r\n`nvim_win_set_config()`. (otherwise the config of a window with `kWinStyleUnused`\r\nwill not unset the `kWinStyleMinimal` style of another window if passed to\r\n`nvim_win_set_config()`, for example)\r\n\r\nFixes #38120\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38122#discussion_r2869972401"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/38122"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/2869972401"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "As `style=\"\"` has always been valid (meaning `kWinStyleUnused`), I've documented it.\r\nThough maybe it'd be better as \"none\" instead, like is done for `border`?",
            "commit_id": "56deca4ba925b0b548ea8ce995817519d530b753",
            "created_at": "2026-03-01T23:17:42Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -728,6 +728,9 @@ Dict(win_config) nvim_win_get_config(Window window, Arena *arena, Error *err)\n   /// Keep in sync with WinSplit in buffer_defs.h\n   static const char *const win_split_str[] = { \"left\", \"right\", \"above\", \"below\" };\n \n+  /// Keep in sync with WinStyle in buffer_defs.h\n+  static const char *const win_style_str[] = { \"\", \"minimal\" };",
